data.description: Very Motivated Seller! Submit your offer! Beautifully restored 1929 Character Spanish-style corner lot home in vibrant and historical Pasadena. This three-bedroom, two-bath gem is not just move-in ready; it's fully modernized to meet all your contemporary expectations. Sunlight streams through numerous arched windows, flooding the spacious living area with natural light. The living room offers a stylish barrel ceiling, golden hardwood floors, and a captivating fireplace that takes center stage. The dining room is bathed in sunlight through the pocket windows, invites you to step out onto the expansive front porch through elegant French doors, setting the scene for unforgettable entertainment. In the fully remodeled chef's kitchen, you'll discover sleek granite countertops, a state-of-the-art stainless steel Thermador 6 burner gas stove & with electric oven, water conserving kitchen sink foot pedals and ample storage for all your culinary essentials. Adjacent to the kitchen, a cozy breakfast nook with original built-in cabinetry. Retreat to the primary bedroom, where you'll find a fully remodeled en-suite bathroom with built-ins and a spacious, modern shower. Step into the sunroom for views of the San Gabriel Mountains and your picturesque backyard. The other two bedrooms have been thoughtfully designed, preserving their original character. The hallway, connecting all bedrooms, offers generous storage, a stylish telephone niche, and a spacious pantry adjacent to the kitchen. The laundry room with side by side washer & dryer includes storage cabinets and backyard access. The landscaping not only delights the eye but is also eco-conscious, designed to conserve water and beautifully illuminated with pathway lights and fruit trees. Detached 2 car garage with fully paid off solar panels on the new roof. Close to freeway access, old town Pasadena, schools and shopping. Welcome Home.
